org.jamesframework.core.problems.constraints.validations

Class SimplePenalizingValidation

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.jamesframework.core.problems.constraints.validations.SimplePenalizingValidation
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    PenalizingValidation, Validation

    public class SimplePenalizingValidation
extends Object
implements PenalizingValidation
    A simple penalizing validation object that wraps a boolean value, indicating whether the corresponding solution passed validation, and a double value, indicating the assigned penalty if the solution did not pass validation.
    Author:
    Herman De Beukelaer

    • Constructor Detail

      • SimplePenalizingValidation

        public SimplePenalizingValidation(boolean passed,
                                  double penalty)
        Create a simple penalizing validation with a given boolean value, indicating whether the corresponding solution passed validation, and an assigned penalty. If passed is true the value of penalty is ignored and the penalty is set to 0. In such case, penalty can be set to any value, e.g. -1. If passed is false it is required that penalty is a strictly positive value.
        Parameters:
        passed - boolean value, true if the corresponding solution is valid
        penalty - assigned penalty, ignored if passed is true
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if passed is false but penalty is not strictly positive

    • Method Detail

        public static final SimplePenalizingValidation FAILED(double penalty)
        Creates a simple penalizing validation indicating that the validation failed, where the given strictly positive penalty is assigned.
        Parameters:
        penalty - assigned penalty
        Returns:
        simple penalizing validation where passed() returns false and getPenalty() returns the given strictly positive penalty
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if penalty is not strictly positive
